java.io.Serializable
public class Example1
extends AbstractExample

An outbound-dialing example that uses analog loop-start voice resources to dial an outside number using Call Progress and Analysis. After a connection is made, the remote caller is recorded until they press a DTMF key, the recording is played back to the called party, then the call is automatically hung up.
